        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You came of age when colonialism was in full swing, when all the great powers of Europe raced to grab up as much of Africa, Asia and South America as possible. However, you were just slightly unsuited for most jobs in the colonies. You weren't quite hardy enough to be a soldier, and you didn't have the head for numbers to be a merchant. Yet when you were just on the cusp of adulthood, your true talents revealed themselves - you worked wonderfully as a subversive agent. Sent into an area, you could quickly and easily disrupt the local governments enough to make it much easier for your own government to roll in. You might have lived and died at your post except when you were sent to South America. At first threatened, the local shadowy agents of power soon realized your true talents. And what's one more colonial casualty, lost to the savage jungle? You weren't entirely pleased at first with the clan that picked you - why did it have to be the ugly ones? But your sire and brood mates soon taught you what brotherhood truly meant. Yet while many of them are content to linger in the sewers, you insist on a more refined image to present to the world. While you, as always, employ your time-tested tactics of spycraft and subversion against your enemies. Cicatriz has ordered you to accompany Priscus Monroe north, knowing that the direct Lasombra will need a solid left hand helping her out. Find those who can do what you do, or be trained to do so, and convince them to help the war effort in San Diego."
